document.title: State of California Student Leadership Standards

85498DF7ADA142DCA5C548B52EDF1090.description:
The student leader acknowledges that images/video of students and staff should never be
presented in such a way that would embarrass or humiliate.

06E6FEE399F24674A57C6B08A32A9D9E.description:
The student leader demonstrates an understanding of the law and school/district policy
regarding the public sharing of images/video of minors on social media and in other public
forums, and works with school administration to protect student privacy.Â

32D08A8DBCCF4AD59D3A614C2C1AFDC5.description:
The student leader includes a diverse cross-section of the student body when creating video
or photo presentations to be shared school-wide.

F37F7E8D5B8C4D66AC455D8F17E0F5FE.description:
The student leader demonstrates a basic understanding of video and photography skills as
they relate to their role on the student leadership team.

F73E604049424478A52AFA99232BA3DA.description:
The student leader recognizes the role of video and photography in the promotion of positive
school culture.

203A70D2507242F0AFA5F39504D61034.description:
Video and Photography: As access to technology grows, student leaders are increasingly using visual/media arts to
promote a positive culture and climate at their schools. These tools have the power to connect
students to their school, but care must be taken to use these tools responsibly, and in a way
that is always positive and inclusive.

270F3792E110499E90BED747BBA74E7A.description:
The student leader demonstrates an understanding of the basic setup of an audio/visual
presentation and can connect a video source to both an audio and a video projection system.

3134ACE5B9BF4CE9AE20FA40EE07CD75.description:
The student leader selects music and other media that are appropriate for the nature of the
event, as well as to the values of the school community and the audience present at the event.

126560E1D7224B1B9E29167C882931B9.description:
The student leader demonstrates an understanding of the basic functions of a sound system
and can set up music and a microphone for any occasion.

966A38D7BAC046859384A4192C8A8A01.description:
The student leader creates an inclusive audio/visual environment that is accessible to all
audience members.

F5CD95924F0948469004133703ECE0F5.description:
The student leader recognizes the positive role of audio/visual technology in the creation of
school events.

9E997F2309054819A31FB5CC97A32268.description:
Audio/Visual Presentation: Student leaders are frequently called upon to not only use video and amplified sound in rallies,
assemblies, and outdoor activities, but also to set up the technology needed for these events as
well. The student leader should have the basic skills to set up this technology, as well as know
how to get the right music started to set the tone for the event.

4CD39BE5E92D4949BC1C982D28590E88.description:
The student leader manages personal data to maintain digital privacy and security for
themselves and for others.

F30E1B6C64BA497FA2411A1502D1993A.description:
The student leader demonstrates an understanding of and respect for the rights and
obligations of using and sharing intellectual property.Â

C698F42118754C919A5C2ECFD2EA83E4.description:
The student leader engages in positive, safe, legal, and ethical behavior when using
technology, including social interactions online or when using networked devices.

883A4D56F31B4BF7A2EE7188F6941A04.description:
The student leader cultivates and manages their digital identity and reputation, and
demonstrates awareness of the permanence of their actions in the digital world.

E9A882BF8EA14349998A14FA34313076.description:
Digital Citizenship: Whether on a shared classroom computer, at home, or on a mobile device, student leaders
have the power to connect to each other and to the world in ways that we never did at their
age. With this power comes the responsibility to understand their own digital footprint, as well
as to treat others with kindness, dignity, and respect.Â

5F5C7643BD67437B8DEA76B32DD893A0.description:
The student leader grants view, comment, and/or edit access to files as needed to allow for
collaboration with the student leadership team.

70713A8EAD354D418E309504CA63CA6E.description:
The student leader stores work in a shared cloud environment that is accessible by
themselves, their leadership team peers, and leadership team educators.Â

9B5221DAE2F641DFB1BC0C8B85F92B9F.description:
The student leader demonstrates a working knowledge of word processing, spreadsheets,
presentations, online forms, and desktop publishing as it relates to their role on the leadership
team.

6C98FC138E9B4C1E9A5F9496F1FBBD36.description:
Digital Workspace and Collaboration: It seems as though cloud technology was made for student leaders. The ability to collaborate
on budgets, scripts, to-do lists, calendars, and surveys, just to name a few, helps student
leaders to focus less on the back-and-forth of comparing different versions of documents, and
more on producing a better digital product to serve the student body. Comments, version
tracking, editing/suggesting mode, in-document chat, and other features enhance the student
leadersâ ability to communicate and collaborate whether in the same room, on a home
computer, or on their mobile device.

05021235BD6E4A619DD95DB25B02B028.description:
The student leader follows federal and state laws and district policy related to food and
beverage sales that take place during the school day.Â

4C09A0B5B62949E3BDF672A6641C7C53.description:
The student leader researches and tracks legislative bills and legal proceedings/judgements
that may influence student body activities, participation, procedures/codes, fundraising, or
accounting.

8E8FF1DF84C8437CAA9B52F22101D013.description:
The student leader adheres to federal, state, and local tax codes as they relate to student
body funds, funding, sponsorship, and re-sale permits.

A1BCCB0F10E44DD493E4D9C0C3B08813.description:
Business Law: In California and across the country, nutrition laws and accounting best practices have changed
dramatically in the last twenty years. Due to increased accountability and more rigorous
oversight, the student leader learns quickly that you canât simply sell chocolate bars on campus
or nachos and soda at lunch to raise money. Awareness of business law, specifically as it
relates to nutrition and student body fund accounting, means that student leaders have a
greater awareness of how they can properly raise funds while preserving their California
non-profit status and complying with school, district, and state laws and policies.Â

AD05E1D4FDCF471798636F92B19C1D59.description:
The student leader attends to the needs of others in a positive manner in recognizing their
role as a representative of the entire student body, school, and community.Â

6149D88F4B6446BFA3A99D105720F2ED.description:
The student leader tracks and archives event participation data to identify trends in event
effectiveness and student engagement.

3242A5138E984F90BC4E93087D9692EB.description:
The student leader develops and implements crowd management and event safety plans
that include a mixture of structural (gates and barriers) and articulated (signage and
announcements) strategies.

B5EF8AE651494EB4A7CEC181A49AB9AD.description:
The student leader communicates with the public regarding current sales and offerings, and
develops a forum for customer feedback.

0669C0116B214C999A6C034C970CEFFD.description: The student leader exhibits positive customer interaction skills.

D6D72098A48D4E57ADF59E73D367FC56.description:
The student leader demonstrates the skills and competencies necessary to recognize
customer concerns and act to reach a satisfactory solution.

0DBD7BFFE1CF49E7A44AC4129970374A.description:
Customer Service:Â Student leaders are in sales. They sell tickets to dances and athletic events, fundraiser items,
spirit wear and student store items. They also âsellâ free items--attendance at assemblies and
rallies, attendance at lunchtime activities, and in general the more abstract concepts of school
spirit and school involvement. Understanding who their clients are, what they want, and how
the expect to be treated helps the student leader to not only create products and experiences
that will better engage their customers in the short term, but will give them sales and customer
service experience they can carry with them into a future career.

4CDA2AD6919E4925B4CB94A75694CF1C.description:
The student leader experiments with different displays/product placement to produce
optimal interest and results.

6E0456326D5C442698AB2ABA7CD13C72.description: The student leader demonstrates creative ways to advertise.Â

E911A385776649E59179A12F10FAAEAA.description:
The student leader utilizes a variety of techniques and media to deliver the message to the
target audience.

138762C29A5D4A10B1F645F63844AFE5.description:
The student leader creates advertisements that are grammatically correct and visually
appealing.

3436208EB55E4A7694B3B7FFB6D4CDC3.description:
The student leader makes sure each advertisement contains all necessary information for
the product or event.

85943C51A78B4B188F5328DA46046457.description: The student leader identifies a target audience for each advertisement.Â

A092CC3528E84ECCB0FED42983D9A52E.description:
Advertising: Advertising is one part of your marketing strategy, specifically designed to sell or promote a
product or activity. Modern advertising blends the more traditional media of posters and flyers
with video production, photography, and social media. An effective advertising begins with
accurate and well-articulated information and comes to life with creativity and sensory appeal.

73C9C70083A94B68A90311A7D21A8620.description:
The student leader systematically develops and implements a marketing plan to deliver the
brand and/or marketing message to the target audience.

BB003B34E4894E7F96DDE807B6481307.description:
The student leader works collaboratively with the student leadership team to create a brand
and/or marketing message for the student leadership team, the student body, the school,
and/or school events.Â

2B3B4E43FBD34BC8A808B9568DB3475A.description: The student leader recognizes the difference between marketing and advertising.

C1758783855049A792A3FA8AC8210459.description:
Marketing: Marketing is a broad strategy. It involves the creation and nurturing of a brand and brand
message that connects the producer (student leaders) to their consumers. The American
Marketing Association defines it as âthe activity, set of institutions, and processes for creating,
communicating, delivering, and exchanging offerings that have value for customers, clients,
partners, and society at large.âÂ

E6050C94C56C4D108348C1EF999F4DC6.description:
The student leader evaluates each fundraising activityâs effectiveness for profitability and
efficient use of human and site resources.

2084B7F318294CC58AFD18B59E9A20D4.description:
The student leader serves as both a participant and leader in various fundraising activities
and employs effective sales techniques.

AD8819CCD7A842A791B02B0DF800E3C3.description:
The student leader orders merchandise and coordinates merchandise design and logistics
with vendors.

3E079ACA1BA74D30B42856E99DB55800.description:
The student leader projects income and expenses within a comprehensive pre-fundraiser
evaluation.Â

D6575CD738994D088E74A32BA7AC298C.description:
The student leader performs market research and identifies trends in student purchasing
preferences when selecting products and vendors for fundraising purposes.

AA4101E552284D28B2C9841445E7F080.description:
The student leader adheres to relevant laws, school board policies, and fiscal accountability
guidelines when selecting appropriate fundraising activities (i.e. state food guidelines,
recommended list of allowable-risk activities, etc.)

E76941AD02554DFF8F72028E94F2844D.description:
Fundraising: Building a successful leadership and activities program requires resources. While the LCAP and
LCFF have unlocked new discretionary resources for site administrators to use in promoting a
more positive school culture, the funding for these programs most often falls to a schoolâs
associated student body. Student leaders who learn effective fundraising practices and
techniques not only help bring in this much-needed revenue, but learn skills they can use in
college, career, and beyond.

A8FED901B90F4045B8010419B4C3B340.description:
The student leader identifies the various sources of school and student funding, the laws
and policies that dictate their allocation, and the structures/channels available for student input
and advocacy.

64823B44844A4EA8AABF6F9C862388FF.description:
The student leader consults the student body on budgetary decisions through the
representative process, public meeting, and open fiscal accountability, and spends student
body funds for the betterment of the student body.Â

D9DF6C55DBFB4BCD8D44072B008D9354.description: The student leader maintains accurate and accessible financial documents.

80064336D84A45E489297D63D1E142C1.description:
The student leader follows student body accounting procedures when performing
bookkeeping tasks, making purchases, receiving and disbursing funds, and reimbursing
vendors.

B0E125B7EA52459AA7302DD6877646D5.description: The student leader tracks income and expenses and identifies profit and loss.

66084140E84D4A46A7B6930CA0D7E28C.description:
The student leader evaluates past budgetary practices and collaborates on creating a
working budget for the current term.Â

83B47733CC20416E8234DE268B392619.description:
The student leader adheres to relevant laws, school board policy, and fiscal accountability
guidelines when managing the student body account.

343D3D894F7749AF80C77D2719554BA5.description:
Finance/Accounting: With a combination of school activities, athletics, and class activities, an associated student
body in California can easily have a six- or seven-digit figure annual budget to manage. School
staff (including administrators, athletic directors, leadership advisor, and account clerk or other
classified staff) often handle many of the day-to-day ASB transactions. However, students in
middle and high school ASBs are still considered by state law to be the stewards of all student
body funds. As such, student leaders should be involved at every level of student body fund
accounting, from the creation and approval of an budget, through the pre-approval and
disbursement of funds, and the collection of fundraiser monies, as well as the record-keeping of
all approvals through the ASB minutes.Â

1FBB1BFD62DD48C3AF133703CD437B02.description:
The student leader utilizes inclusive meeting strategies for brainstorming, prioritizing, and
project planning.Â

FB0A1D5FE55D40989F0FB66810C30B20.description: The student leader creates relevant agendas and maintains accurate minutes.

7460C64F7D9C41B79570890E4305CDB0.description: The student leader practices Parliamentary Procedure during formal business meetings.

9851F329E2C748CDA0E876CAD3D3A3D1.description: The student leader utilizes the principles of group dynamics in meeting protocols.Â

4AE88A95F93E408F91B342FCABE8F429.description:
Effective Meetings: The Business Meeting often serves as the backbone of the daily operation of student leadership
organizations. The adult advisor, the president, the secretary, and each individual member all
have a role to play in a productive meeting. By understanding the format and structure of an
effective meeting, student leaders can give all stakeholders a voice and more quickly get to the
planning and implementation of the programs and activities that create a positive school
culture.Â

79F602463CD74C2FB6209B5E2BECF71B.description:
The student leader chosen to participate on a selection committee shall practice fairness,
impartiality, open-mindedness, and confidentiality during and after the selection process.

3A35F1F956F7471680DDA3D79B075B31.description:
The student leader constructs a campaign speech or presentation and/or participates in an
interview process.

1AE6CF422EA643F7AD32B128F948D822.description: The student leader practices positive marketing and campaigning.Â

FF64A6212FC742A98C29479A8F0FD764.description:
The student leader campaigns and markets fairly in accordance with the school constitution
and bylaws.

3768927EC9D34E178F494022EF1896CA.description:
The student leader can articulate the purpose of a representative government and the
workings of a democracy.

35EE5C26E8384FF391D3D40B5DB3889F.description:
Elections and Appointments: When a student leader runs or applies for an elected or appointed office and wins, she wants to
know that she did so in a fair and equitable process. Likewise, the student who runs/applies
and does not get the job also wants to know that he lost fair and square. While the primary
responsibility for ensuring a fair and accessible election/selection process rests with the advisor
and administration, student leaders can contribute a great deal to the fairness and equality of
the process by following the rules and guidelines, encouraging their friends and supporters to
positively participate in the process, and then finally being a gracious winner or loser.Â

A8FB80CB2A964A7DA57312A829CA2C0D.description:
The student leader follows the established chain of command protocol for the student
leadership team, the school, and the school district.

58FB8DD5D80B4F9BB61B01F28286D155.description:
The student leader contributes to the creation of rules, regulations, agreements, and
contracts for student-led activities.

F1DF1B09919843BEB62AB2C8D64FD80F.description:
The student leader recognizes the ethical and legal implications of following or not following
established procedures, rules, regulations, agreements, and contracts.

1617BB4E0BC2483E8F80D8AE4460A322.description:
Procedures: Adherence to established policies and procedures is an important aspect of local, regional, and
national government. Teaching our students to identify and follow these formal and informal
protocols is an important part of their growth as entrusted leaders.

EC6C15C51C8C4829BF4FBE9C26130080.description:
The student leader acknowledges the right of students to form student clubs and
organizations in accordance with district, state, and federal guidelines.

EA10BCF2B9DF45B1B5664498644A75C5.description:
The student leader contributes to committees and/or councils and recognizes how the
committees and/or councils benefit the student leadership team.Â

F20694C1F763424F96E4562A97D8B6A2.description: The student leader reviews and/or creates a constitution and bylaws for the student body.

D0326FC40B154587A2D3D17F65420A76.description:
The student leader learns the chain of command that exists within their school and their
student body organization.

740209704EC946F1BCD97D2F86E574D6.description:
The student leader acknowledges the relationship of power and authority between the
student body organization, school staff, school district governing board, and state legislature.

4CC21CCBA5604FF394F9B0ABF8BA45D2.description:
The student leader identifies the purpose and function of government, the scope and limits
of authority, and the principle of âconsent of the governed.âÂ

CA3B2D2134C8452C930E73C49A59EDD5.description:
Authority and Governance: Student leadership offers our kids the opportunity to participate in the system of government
and procedures that exist on their campuses. It also allows them to make comparisons between
student government and local, state, and national government systems and policies, and to
experience the constraints within all government systems must operate.Â

5B48A884DAED487792A7A774FF218DDA.description:
The student leader demonstrates empathy for, and an awareness of social, cultural, and
societal norms for diverse locations and populations.

6AD73721B8284E0A9917A10867F1AB85.description: The student leader experiences and recognizes the benefit of serving others.

C1D7564792C34AED9A2DD04224C56641.description:
The student leader participates in a service activity or project to serve a specific need of
others.

475325A8DB1E4A799AA42A8C94754CC2.description:
The student leader establishes relationships with community leaders and community groups
to help address a community need.

11E54D70EF034F18884A932D1A9CCAAE.description:
Community Service: Serving others creates connections and awakens a sense of responsibility for societal
challenges. It also helps the leader identify needs within the community and fosters the
development of empathy and compassion.

37AE2E9BF7E24124A3A6BB40AFB5B8FA.description:
The student leader seeks both school and community feedback to evaluate and reflect upon
the impact of the project.

C17B30FCE6014B4FAA70AA080D59257F.description:
The student leader develops and implements a research-based plan of action to address a
specific community need.

A83FA45990DB4138947925F9F02915D5.description:
Utilizing academic skills, the student leader researches various solutions to a local need, and
integrates academic research into a service learning study.Â

1FB99D4CFA524044BA1588B2CBB277E2.description:
The student leader assesses the needs of the community by reaching out to community
leaders and local government.

F48266797CF94E2EA3E2F213DFB1144E.description:
The student leader recognizes the difference between service learning and community
service.

34C0C0E4E3684749B49B7300D31EDF92.description:
Service Learning Strategies: Informed global citizens need practical experiences -- at an early age, to effect change in their
communities and beyond. Fostering these opportunities (and follow up reflection) empowers
them to identify their responsibilities as members of the global community.Â

E26DFA15050847298CDD247CC1D0779D.description:
The student leader analyzes different forms of civic activism and ways in which citizens can
effect change in society.

B1AEBD92EA394D2781A7306C24F5DB54.description:
The student leader recognizes the value of membership in, and/or partnership with,
associations--groups of people organized for a joint purpose.

DCC484400C2E4B5C91F05D7FC0F71BBF.description: The student leader identifies the financial restrictions and guidelines of other organizations.Â

764FB8D1A54A42C4B3E796D5CF071C24.description:
The student leader develops partnerships with various student, school, parent, and
community groups.Â

C16AF6317E5F4159B445E6BFE829F6B8.description:
The student leader acknowledges differing backgrounds (cultural, religious, geographic,
special needs, socio-economic, gender identity, sexual orientation) and includes diverse
perspectives to promote an inclusive school culture.Â

1F242781E993439EA7E5152F46AAA48E.description:
The student leader identifies differing social and cultural norms and then raises awareness of
those norms to promote acceptance and inclusion.

AD481E49B5274BB08A9D6D309D3E9B3F.description: The student leader seeks and offers help when needed.

3BF591643F5A400C8D39913B386E89C8.description: The student leader negotiates conflict constructively.Â

C6EC8C54AC0C46B29247DA105A1AE0DE.description: The student leader resists inappropriate social pressure.

A396FBCD76B94517B1DBCAF4C36910BE.description:
The student leader establishes and maintains healthy relationships with the student
leadership team, the student body, and adults.

000A7DEBD1954462867B07F7E313D934.description:
The student leader makes informed decisions about behavior and social interactions that
consider the consequences of oneâs actions and the well-being of oneself and others.Â

98696BDE503044D2A01B09EE0F5A565B.description:
The student leader will practice self-management by regulating thoughts, emotions, and
behaviors in various situations as they relate to stress, motivation, discipline, and impulse
control.Â

FF047E1FA2114547A210968BF9E3C7C5.description:
The student leader analyzes oneâs strengths and areas of improvement to develop a
validated self-perception, self-competence, and growth mindset.Â

4282BDB9B75B459486D5C3C9D3679F25.description:
The student leader identifies emotions, thoughts, and values that impact behavior and self
efficacy.Â

4B87FF0EAF0342F2A43E84F85BFA17C3.description:
Social and Emotional Learning:Â A harmonious environment where all leaders feel validated, accepted, and important is
necessary to facilitate cooperation within the group. Individual leaders need to develop self
awareness and an appreciation for the diversity of others in order to utilize their strengths and
contribute positively to the group.

1D8A6ED9CAD44FCA864BA65ED5B29134.description: The student leader gives feedback to peers in a positive and constructive manner.

DB8F26F018B440A288C9FC4502121CEC.description:
The student leader self-evaluates, solicits peer and advisor feedback, and makes
adjustments to goals, behavior, and processes as necessary.

DA75ED2766CE4B43B8C75FB1B413DFEE.description:
The student leader creates timelines for meeting goals and monitors progress to ensure
on-time completion.

5D0F862F998A4492A2A76FA425888E96.description: The student leader creates a plan of action for achieving goals.Â

4ED43779F887468F889C19159F621D4D.description: The student leadership team sets attainable goals to improve school culture and climate.

35A372AB14F14D14AD3A53DFB90A0C12.description: The student leader sets short-term and long-term personal goals.Â

C0ACE5A0BDA7493D8D28FC11DCFF7F77.description:
Goal Setting, Feedback, and Evaluation: Identifying vision and a systematic plan for implementation of the teamâs goals leads to its
ultimate success. The team should first identify why its mission is important and then set
attainable goals to achieve its objectives.

8B0C93ABEDD34D4AA496EA8F73BFB122.description: Once made, the student leader supports decisions of the group.

71B10E637E5E45A788199B594A1121B2.description:
The student leader considers diverse ideas, synthesizes viewpoints, and analyzes claims and
evidence on all sides of an issue when considering possible solutions.Â

A508A70EA8344A98B1A32443FD3BACB8.description:
The student leader recognizes and utilizes various models of decision-making (e.g.,
authoritative, consensus, democratic, individual)Â

04306137C6CF4CD58254F8B3CCC8FA84.description: The student leader delegates authority when appropriate.

DF3C733F98FF4A458EF91370286363B1.description: The student leader celebrates accomplishments and recognizes the contributions of others.

5AC230D29FB446DD8CFE37156A222E91.description: The student leader enlists others to share a common vision.

661D68B42E494A12AD210D85F4E9F915.description: The student leader serves as a participating member of a group.Â

74D3AF4524EA423F964F8CB6F0B2D5BB.description:
The student leader assumes a leadership role in an activity or group work that allows them to
facilitate and direct the groupâs activities.

4014FB81E3654EA68DD3A3951D35068B.description:
The student leader appreciates the diversity of others, and the value of representing a
diverse student body.

841088CC05134037981773861D84A1B2.description:
The student leader acknowledges different personality types and how to work together in an
all-inclusive group setting.

66ED76DC08CE456F9204CD485DEF003D.description:
Group Dynamics: Effective leaders work collaboratively to create vision, purpose, and direction for their team.
Particular emphasis on positive group dynamics leads to the best possible outcome for the
teamâs mission.Â

500A5417D90047019DA9CA639B203831.description:
The student leader acknowledges and celebrates the strengths and accomplishments of
others.Â

5134E7D859474F13A1BABD11E97AEA9C.description:
The student leader takes initiative by assessing where a need exists, and assisting without
being asked, when appropriate.Â

46156A51A6C740119B143E3FF15E1411.description:
The student leader utilizes a combination of traditional, non-traditional, and other creative
approaches to idea generation, activity planning, and problem solving.Â

024AEEA98A1446E7B4ECB1C42FA0CDFD.description:
The student leader practices problem solving skills, including identifying the problem,
soliciting possible solutions from members of the leadership team, and then implementing an
agreed-upon solution.

FAC75FCF4F254A5589A32C40CE572664.description: The student leader communicates feelings using âIâ statements.

E01094D498E245E086E7A3F4373AC0B8.description: The student leader treats others with compassion and empathy.

FBF79F0F0F9F40658FF2602D003E4DE0.description:
The student leader articulates their own point of view and utilizes active listening to hear
othersâ points of view to arrive at a mutual decision.

F2AA13E9968D45FC93C7CB50CC2D463B.description:
The student leader practices active listening skills, including positive facial expression, eye
contact, posture, summarizing, and eliminating distractions.Â

06794603903D40B4949512962BF09C51.description: The student leader understands the difference between passive and active listening.Â

7ABE8BB06FBE4A4888F370D272CBE160.description:
The student leader acknowledges the value of teamwork and consensus building in all
aspects of student leadership.

D525638AA2E34FEA868855D4FE06EB29.description:
Interpersonal Skills: Strong leaders possess exceptional interpersonal skills that focus on active listening, taking
initiative, and collaborating positively.Â

AF73EB3978994BF186FF066DC9517CAB.description:
The student leader seeks out evaluation and feedback from previous events to inform the
planning and implementation of future events.

EABE44DBC6604F19A7429850ACFAEE16.description:
Periodically, the student leader evaluates the job performance of their leadership peers to
